- CK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1382<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/8/02 10:22:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3537.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Names...</span><hr size=1> GM's wouldn't allow my DE SK to have the last name A'Leval, even though this was his name for years in D&amp;D where it was an actual surname in Menzobarranzan, without the '.  I was able to keep Aleval, but it seemed silly I couldn't throw in the apostrophe like DE's do. <p>-- The <select><option>SOB</option><option>Grump</option><option>Bastard</option><option>pwner of Chiteng</option></select> formerly known as Raedwulf</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 619<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/8/02 10:52:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3537.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Names...</span><hr size=1> When the naming policy first started getting enforced with any regularity, D'names were still allowed, even if they made phrases...Then they started not allowing names that made D'phrases but people who already had these names were grandfathered, some still got through because guides were not enforcing the letter of the law and still sometimes let names that were blatantly 'the' names were given....Now, I believe the policy is that absolutly no use of 'D`' 'De' or anything else that remotely resembles 'the' but people who had their names prior to the new enforcement were allowed to keep it.<br>
<br>
It used to be and may still be that if the GMs didnt catch you with a naming violation by the time you were level 35, they considered it grandfathered. Of course, offensive naming violations were not grandfathered. I don't know if the current policy which the gm's enforce still respects the grandfathered policy, but I believe it does.<br>
<br>
Remember that any name that has a tick mark in it had to have been given by a GM at one time and these names were not always against the policy. As long as a GM gave them the name, they will not likely take it away unless it is vulgar and they somehow missed that fact when they gave it.<br>
